"><b>BENCHMARK CODE</b></span></td><td bordercolor="black" width="75%" align="center" bgcolor="#CCCCCC"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial"><b>BENCHMARK</b></span></td></tr></table><table align="center" width="100%" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#000000"><tr><td width="25%" align="center" Valign="top"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">SC.6.CS.1.1</span></td><td width="75%"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">Define the states of data.<br /><br /><i><u>Clarifications</u></i>:<br/><i>Clarification 1:</i> States of data include data at rest, data in motion and data in use.</span></td></tr></table><table align="center" width="100%" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#000000"><tr><td width="25%" align="center" Valign="top"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">SC.6.CS.1.2</span></td><td width="75%"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">Illustrate the concept of access control and how to limit access to authorized users.</span></td></tr></table><table align="center" width="100%" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#000000"><tr><td width="25%" align="center" Valign="top"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">SC.6.CS.1.3</span></td><td width="75%"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">Discuss the importance of cybersecurity.</span></td></tr></table><table align="center" width="100%" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#000000"><tr><td width="25%" align="center" Valign="top"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">SC.6.CS.1.4</span></td><td width="75%"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">Determine information that should remain confidential.</span></td></tr></table><table align="center" width="100%" border="1" style="border-collapse: